{
  "prompt": "A technical side view line drawing of a step-through electric bicycle frame with no top tube, featuring a mid-drive motor mounted at the bottom bracket area. The rear suspension is clearly illustrated, using a swingarm and centrally mounted rear shock absorber. The drawing includes precise mechanical details, showing the motor casing, down tube integration, and smooth frame curvature to accommodate a low standover height. Designed for a 20-inch fat tire, urban delivery e-bike.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A black-and-white technical line drawing of an electric bicycle with a motorcycle-style frame design. The frame has no top tube, and instead features a reinforced, curved downtube and underframe that supports the central mid-drive motor. The rear suspension is a mono-shock system connected to a swingarm. The battery is mounted low in the downtube. The overall look blends motorcycle and bicycle engineering, optimized for urban delivery use. The tires are 20-inch with a 3.0 width, suitable for urban on-road performance.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A black-and-white technical side drawing of a step-through frame electric bike, without a top tube. The frame features a mid-drive motor mounted near the bottom bracket, a rear suspension coil shock, and 20-inch wheels. The design emphasizes a low standover height for easy access, mimicking a motorcycle-inspired geometry with a solid downtube and curved seat stays. The image is a clean, precise engineering diagram with detailed components and line clarity.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
